descp2: int, RandomState instance or None, optional, default None The seed of the pseudo random number generator for adding small noise to continuous variables in order to remove repeated values. If int, random_state is the seed used by the random number generator; If RandomState instance, random_state is the random number generator; If None, the random number generator is the RandomState instance used by `np.random`.
